name: Hictober #5
description:
Raven

This is Muninn, one of the ravens of Odin. Muninn means memory, mind, and that’s why I like him more than Huginn. Memory is what makes people who they are.
The berry in his beak is the memory which keeps one awake at night. You know, “do you remember how you made fool of yourself in the sixth grade?” - that kind of memory. Muninn carries it around so that you could never forget it.
